# GPU support for all three vendors from one ISO.
# NVIDIA proprietary lives in nvidia.list.chroot + the gaming hook (32-bit).
# AMD (amdgpu) and Intel (i915) are driven entirely by Mesa: 64-bit here, and
# 32-bit (for Proton/Wine) from the gaming hook, which is where i386 multiarch
# gets enabled — package lists install too early for :i386 entries.
# A first-boot detector (archonsync-gpu-detect) neutralises NVIDIA-only config
# on machines that have no NVIDIA card.

# Mesa OpenGL + Vulkan (64-bit).
mesa-vulkan-drivers
libgl1-mesa-dri
libvulkan1
vulkan-tools

# Hardware video decode (smooth, low-CPU YouTube/Twitch/streams).
mesa-va-drivers
intel-media-va-driver-non-free
va-driver-all
vainfo

# Diagnostics.
mesa-utils
clinfo
